    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Auxiliary Countershaft Assembly</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the bolts and both countershaft rear bearing covers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301899">Figure 99</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301899" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301899" filename="../figg13/G1301899.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 99. Remove Bolts and Countershaft Rear Bearing Covers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the snap ring from the groove at rear of each countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018a0">Figure 100</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018a0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018a0" filename="../figg13/G13018A0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 100. Remove Snap Ring From Rear Countershaft Groove</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the countershafts forward far enough to partially unseat
                the rear bearings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018a1">Figure 101</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018a1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018a1" filename="../figg13/G13018A1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 101. Drive Countershafts Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Using caution so as not to damage the bearing inner race on the front of each countershaft,
                drive the shafts to the rear to expose the bearing snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018a2">Figure 102</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018a2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018a2" filename="../figg13/G13018A2.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 102. Drive Shafts to Rear to Expose Bearing Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a puller to remove the countershaft rear bearings from the housing bores (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13018a3">Figure 103</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13018a3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13018a3" filename="../figg13/G13018A3.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 103. Remove Countershaft Rear Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The auxiliary countershaft assembly CANNOT be removed from the housing until the splitter
                        shift yoke is removed.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
